 \u003ca href=\"https://www.carscoops.com/tag/amazon/\"\u003eAmazon Prime\u003c/a\u003e customers can save $1 per gallon of fuel at more than 7,500 BP, Amoco, or AMPM stations. Customers can get a maximum of 35 gallons, which works out to be a savings of $35.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMore: \u003ca href=\"https://www.carscoops.com/2024/10/amazon-prime-members-now-get-10-cent-per-gallon-discount-on-gasoline/\"\u003eAmazon Prime Members Now Save 10¢ Per Gallon On Gas, EV Charging Perks Coming Soon\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eNeedless to say, this is a huge discount as the national average price for a gallon of gasoline is $3.16. With Prime, that falls to $2.16 for the holiday weekend.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhile Prime members typically save ten cents per gallon, the latest promotion is sure to draw plenty of attention. However, if you’ve never used Prime at the pump before, there are a few things you need to know.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n        \u003ca href=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Amazon-Prime-Fuel-Discount-703-1.jpg\" data-type=\"inarticle-image-block\"\u003e \n            \u003cfigure\u003e\n                \u003cpicture\u003e\n                    \u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2025/07/Amazon-Prime-Fuel-Discount-703-1.webp 2500w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2025/07/Amazon-Prime-Fuel-Discount-703-1-400x93.webp 400w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2025/07/Amazon-Prime-Fuel-Discount-703-1-1024x239.webp 1024w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2025/07/Amazon-Prime-Fuel-Discount-703-1-768x179.webp 768w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2025/07/Amazon-Prime-Fuel-Discount-703-1-1536x359.webp 1536w, https://www.carscoops.com/wp-content/uploads/webp/2025/07/Amazon-Prime-Fuel-Discount-703-1-2048x478.webp 2048w\" s